00:13:10.000 --> 00:13:14.000
And, depending on what the particle
size is, we end up with two

00:13:14.000 --> 00:13:18.000
conditions, and I want you to be
aware of these because there is some

00:13:18.000 --> 00:13:22.000
interesting physics involved.
And, what we're talking about here

00:13:22.000 --> 00:13:26.000
is dispersions.
It's a dispersion because we don't

00:13:26.000 --> 00:13:51.750
have homogeneity.
Dispersion is fine particles.

00:13:51.750 --> 00:13:59.250
And I'm using the term particle to
mean this cluster,

00:13:59.250 --> 00:14:06.750
fine particles distributed
throughout some matrix.

00:14:06.750 --> 00:14:14.250
And, what's the principle behind
this? Why doesn't everything just

00:14:14.250 --> 00:14:21.750
settle out? Well,
here's what's going on.

00:14:21.750 --> 00:14:29.250
When we look at a foreign particle,
this is this cluster that's on the

00:14:29.250 --> 00:14:34.880
order of 2 to beyond even 1,000 nm.
And, why is this suspended in

00:14:34.880 --> 00:14:38.660
solution in the first place?
Because we know we've got two

00:14:38.660 --> 00:14:42.440
forces acting on it.
First of all, we've got a gravity

00:14:42.440 --> 00:14:46.220
force, which is acting to cause this
to settle. So,

00:14:46.220 --> 00:15:05.906
this is a settling force thanks to
the gravity field.

00:14:30.000 --> 00:14:55.810
And, working in the other direction,
this interface between the insoluble

00:14:55.810 --> 00:15:01.630
and the solvent,
along that interface we have binding

00:15:01.630 --> 00:15:07.450
forces as well.
And these binding forces I'll

00:15:07.450 --> 00:15:13.270
simply call interfacial forces.
And, these interfacial forces want

00:15:13.270 --> 00:15:19.090
to bind the particle to the solvent
at the resistance to

00:15:19.090 --> 00:15:37.280
the gravity field.
So, now, why does particle size come

00:15:04.500 --> 00:15:09.500
in to play? You know the gravity
force is proportional to mass.

00:15:09.500 --> 00:15:14.500
And, the mass of the particle is
proportional to the volume of the

00:15:14.500 --> 00:15:19.500
particle. And volume scales with
the cube of the radius,

00:15:19.500 --> 00:15:24.500
whereas this interfacial force,
as the term implies, interface, the

00:15:24.500 --> 00:15:29.500
interfacial force is proportional to
the area of contact between the

00:15:29.500 --> 00:15:55.160
particle and the solvent.
And, area scales as the square of

00:15:55.160 --> 00:16:01.490
the radius. And you know from your
math that R cubed dominates R

00:16:01.490 --> 00:16:07.830
squared when R is large.
That comes as no surprise.

00:16:07.830 --> 00:16:14.160
But, at very, very small values of
R, R squared dominates R cubed.

00:16:14.160 --> 00:16:20.490
And, depending on what the relative
forces are is going to govern what

00:16:20.490 --> 00:16:26.830
the relative particle size has to be
before we get particles that will be

00:16:26.830 --> 00:16:45.993
suspended in the second phase.
And so, we have here the example of

00:16:12.000 --> 00:16:16.000
the colloids. One example of the
colloid is milk,

00:16:16.000 --> 00:16:20.000
which I described to you already.
And even though we have two phases,

00:16:20.000 --> 00:16:24.000
both transparent to visible light,
that interface scatters the light.

00:16:24.000 --> 00:16:28.000
These particles are large enough
that they can be separated

00:16:28.000 --> 00:16:52.280
by filtration.
But it's unlikely that they'll

00:16:52.280 --> 00:16:56.850
separate in a gravity field owing to
this. They don't settle.

00:16:56.850 --> 00:17:01.420
They don't settle. Actually,
what has happened over the past two

00:17:01.420 --> 00:17:05.990
